div.div:
Improve accuracy with product quantity check in DeviceController
Introduced a verification process in the DeviceController to ensure accuracy in product quantity management. An error response is created if the incremented quantity does not match the predicted quantity.

Refactor PaymentController's OrderPayment instantiation
Cleaned up OrderPayment instantiation and other code enhancements in PaymentController. Replaced fully qualified name of OrderPayment class with a class import statement to enhance readability. In addition, unnecessary event invocation and checks for 'DELIVERED' status have been removed to simplify the code structure and streamline the order handling process.

Update ApiController and PaymentController structure
Added void return type to ApiController constructor and simplified conditions in PaymentController. Removed status check for 'DELIVERED' in refund and cancel order methods of PaymentController, which will now directly change order status to 'REFUNDED' or 'CANCELLED'. The aim is to streamline the order handling process by reducing code complexity.

Add voucherInfo function and order cancellation in controllers
Added the voucherInfo function in the DeviceController and order cancellation and refund functions in the PaymentController. Removed unused UpdateAudit event calls. Primarily divided the routes by adding relevant routing in the backend.php file and ensured permission and data integrity checks remain intact.

Refactor routing structure and update product inventory handling
Divided routes between web.php and a newly introduced backend.php to improve code organization. Made enhancements in the product inventory handling within the ShopProducts list layout and DeviceController, providing more detailed inventory information and refined error handling. Created a new middleware group 'backend' in the HTTP kernel, improving request handling.
